newsitem.title: INDIA: Indian soybean prices steady in dull trade.
newsitem.headline: Indian soybean prices steady in dull trade.

text.p: Soybean prices were steady in limited trading activity in the markets of central India on Thursday. Arrivals was around 8,000 tonnes, dealers said.
Soyoil refined was down by 100 rupees per tonne, while soyoil solvent was unchanged in thin trading.

Soymeal prices were slightly down on very limited exports demand. Soymeal yellow was $272-273 per tonne in export and rapeseed extraction was $134. Rapeseed extraction was 4,575 rupees FOR Bedibunder and 4,550 rupees FOR Bhavnagar. Business volume was dull and the undertone was weak. Offerings from Indian exporters were increased today.
